====== Installing LaueG ======

1) Install SCILAB 5.5.2
	Download scilab-5.5.2_x64.exe from www.scilab.org/download/previous-versions/
	You must install SCILAB before you install LaueG, and it must be v5.5.2

2) Installing LaueG
	Run the setup file "LaueG_setup_<date>.exe"
	If you installed SCILAB "as administrator" you must do the same for LaueG.
	Use the "LaueG" icon on the desktop to run LaueG.
	If you installed LaueG "as administrator" the icon is on the administrator desktop.

First time useage can be very slow, tens of seconds. If a popup window appears
that is completely empty, try randomly clicking on the window. The window
should then show its contents correctly. This should only happen very rarely.

====== Installing LaueTiff ======

LaueTiff is a useful utility where you can right-click on an image file (*.tif)
and it will display the Comments and other useful experimental information for
the image.

1) Copy LaueTiff.exe to C:\windows\system32\
	If you use a different folder, you have to edit the following registry file

2) Run the registry file LaueTiffRightClick.reg
